snippet.textDisplay:
Where the mind is without fear and the head is held high
Where knowledge is free
Where the world has not been broken up into fragments
By narrow domestic walls
Where words come out from the depth of truth
Where tireless striving stretches its arms towards perfection
Where the clear stream of reason has not lost its way
Into the dreary desert sand of dead habit
Where the mind is led forward by thee
Into ever-widening thought and action
Into that heaven of freedom, my Father, let my people awake. 


[Rabindranath Tagore]

snippet.textDisplay:
Though I was not the part of migration, actually born here quite later, but I heard the stories of "Hindustan" from my father who spent his childhood there before the partition. He used to tell me the stories of the people and places of Kheda, District Badayun UP and Delhi in such a way that I always felt myself there. He went back to India in 1960 just after his marriage. Once he told me that he cried a lot when he saw his childhood places.
I can understand the sorrow and the feelings of the people who left everything behind and started a new life in a new country and still their souls are at the birthplace. 
Hats off to Mr. Mishra and his team. Kindly do us a favor, the music sound is very high and diminishing the singers voice.
snippet.textOriginal:
